<hl>
<seg id=1> China and America signed an agreement on high-tech cooperation in Shanghai. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Shanghai, 31 August, by Bai Guoling, Xia Ruhe The Signing Ceremony of Sino-American High-tech Cooperation Agreement took place today in Shanghai. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> This morning the signed two projects were the technology of information and communication network and the biotechnology of deoxyribonucleic acid, and at the same time, they signed the Cooperative Agreement of Language Teaching. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Shanghai Branch of the Central Institute of International Technology and Economy Research of the State Council, Pudong Further Education Center of Shanghai, signed the three projects separately with American Information Network Corporation, the World Learning Organization and Haisac Company. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> At the Signing Ceremony, Chairman of the Information Network Corporation C E Mallet said that it's very important for the two countries to sign the agreements on high-tech projects. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He also expected to build the electronic information highway between America and China, and let New York Stock Exchange and Shanghai Stock Exchange communicate with each other as soon as possible. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Judy Mellow, Chairman of the World Learning Organization expected to set up a joint educational organization in Shanghai at the end of this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> According to the news from the Americans, the three-signed projects were fostered and supported by Minister of Financial Affairs of America, Brown, who had visited Shanghai before. </seg>
</p>
